It is alleged Trevor Davis shot his wife, Elma Davis, before turning the gun on himself at their home on Sunday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Mossel Bay police are investigating a suspected murder-suicide involving a couple well-known in bowling circles. It is alleged Trevor Davis shot his wife, Elma Davis, before turning the gun on himself at their home on Sunday afternoon. “A 67-year-old man and a 52-year-old woman were both found on their bedroom floor with shotgun wounds. A shotgun was found on the scene,” said the police's Pieter Koekemoer. He said they were both declared dead at the scene by medical personnel. 